                            <comment id="486902" author="simmonsja" created="Sat, 7 Feb 2026 18:01:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;pyyaml only installs the libyaml bindings (CLoader &amp;amp; co.) if it finds the libyaml-dev package. If we are going to have pyyaml baed tools then libyaml-dev has to be installed by default.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="486901" author="adilger" created="Sat, 7 Feb 2026 17:09:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=flei&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;flei&quot;&gt;flei&lt;/a&gt;, could you take a look at this, it is causing about 2/3 of test sessions to fail on Ubuntu. It &lt;em&gt;shoukd&lt;/em&gt; be possible to fall back to &lt;tt&gt;Loader&lt;/tt&gt; if &lt;tt&gt;CLoader&lt;/tt&gt; is not available for some reason, but that doesn&apos;t appear to be the case. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=colmstea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;colmstea&quot;&gt;colmstea&lt;/a&gt; it seems like a package may be missing from some of the Ubuntu test nodes?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
